# Errors & Logging

## User-facing errors

{{#if isReact}}
- Use error boundaries for route-level or feature-level failures; never swallow errors silently.
{{/if}}
{{#if isVue}}
- Handle errors with `onErrorCaptured` / global handlers where configured.
{{/if}}
{{#if isSvelteKit}}
- Provide `+error.svelte` pages and meaningful status messages.
{{/if}}
{{#if isAngular}}
- Provide a custom `ErrorHandler` for centralized reporting.
{{/if}}

## Logging

- Log structured context (route, user id if safe, correlation id) — **never** secrets, tokens, or PII.

## Monitoring

{{#if (includes monitoring "sentry")}}
- Capture unhandled promise rejections; tag releases with version/commit.
{{/if}}

## Source maps

- Upload source maps to your error tracker in production builds when privacy policy allows.
